'''Doodnik's Café''' was a small [[Torpedo/Legends|torpedo]]-shaped dining establishment located on the [[Planet/Legends|world]] known as [[Tyne's Horky]]. The proprietor, [[Doodnik Sharpelz]], was a cantankerous [[Jillsarian/Legends|Jillsarian]] who was usually found working behind the counter serving up [[Supernova (beverage)|Supernova]] or [[Photon fizzle]]s.

==History==
Prior to the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], Doodnik temporarily acquired ownership of the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]]. He put them to work as food-servers but disowned them by the end of the day when R2 began spilling drinks on the patrons.

Many of the more underhanded dealings on Tyne's Horky were brokered at Doodnik's. A [[Tammuz-an/Legends|Tammuz-an]] alien named [[Sollag Den]] once met with [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Kleb Zellock]] and hired him to locate the lost Tammuz-an [[Prince/Legends|prince]] [[Mon Julpa]].

Doodnik's was also the site of a scuffle between a local miner named [[Jann Tosh]] and some thugs working under Zellock's employ. A [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] captain named [[Jessica Meade]] burst into Doodnik's and saved young Jann's life.

Doodnik liked to occasionally provide live entertainment for his customers. The [[Max Rebo Band/Legends|Max Rebo Band]] was known to perform there from time to time. Doodnik once commented that a portion of the diner was owned by [[Kleb Zellock]].

==Popular menu items==
Doodnik's had a better reputation for its drinks than its food. Among the more favorable beverages to be found at the diner were:

*[[Photon fizzle]]s
*[[Giva jumbo]]s
*[[Circuit cider]]
*[[Supernova (beverage)|Supernovas]]

